			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Charm Kiting  Lvls 60-65<a name="66733"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 13 04 2:35 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok guys this isn't exactly new but no one else knows about it accept me I guess.  I started doing it when PoP came out and was one of the first bard to lv 65 on my server.  So heres what you do..
<br />

<br />
Pull around 4-5 mobs at once.  Charm one of the mobs to make it your pet and make it attack the one of the mobs that's still pissed at you.  The other should hit your pet also, if they don't join in right away on the beat down, just run it around you pet until it latches on.
<br />

<br />
Watch the pet's life carefully and wait till it's down to like 10-20% life, then release the pet with the level 62 Song: Druzzil's Disillusionment <a target="_new" href="http://eqdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?s=3364&amp;c=1&amp;ForumID=113">http://eqdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?s=3364&amp;c=1&amp;ForumID=113</a>  It used to work with invis but because of the patch on 10/13/04 pets no longer are released from invis.
<br />

<br />
Once the pet is released it's almost dead so all you need to do is kite it around with a some DoT songs to finish it off.  Then rinse and repeat.
<br />

<br />
*Note: This works best when you have a high level mob attacking your pet.  So if you can get a lv 65 mob to attack your level 55 pet, it will loose life really quickly.  A good place to do this I found is in PoN where the Nightmares <a target="_new" href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=10308">http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=10308</a> and Hobgoblins <a target="_new" href="http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=10317">http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=10317</a> are.  Grab one Nightmare and 3 Hobgoblins.
<br />

<br />
*Note: Charm Kiting works really well for all you high level bards with your Voice of the Vampire Song.  The higher level you can charm, the bigger mobs you can charm kite.
<br />

<br />
*Note: Doesn't work well with any caster mobs or summoning mobs, but is still possible.
<br />

<br />
*Note: The hardest thing you'll find is controlling aggro so make sure not to anger any mobs that you want to attack your pet.  Try pulling with a song that doesn't do damage
<br />

<br />
So that's it!  If this technique already exist don't yell at me, cause as far as I know I'm created it.<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /></span></td>
