				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Charm Kiting    A NEW SOLOING TECHNIQUE!!<a name="66771"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 13 04 5:32 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I don't know why you guys have taken such offense to my soloing technique.  Don't bash it until you try it.  It's not a joke.  I seriously do use this to exp.
<br />

<br />
Now someone said that they patched the aggro of mobs?  I don't see how it affects Charm Kiting.  The the mobs will still cling on to your charmed mob, you just need to make it attach one of them and the others will join in on kicking the crap out of you charmed mob.
<br />

<br />
Why wont it work past 66?  I'm only 65 so i wouldn't really know.  I use it at 65 and make about 1 aa ever 2 hours, so it's not bad exp at that level.
<br />

<br />
(edit)  Just talked to one of my friends and he said that the reason it might not work well levels 66+ is because of all the summoning mobs.  But if you can find a camp with some high level mobs without summon then this still works just great.
<br />

<br />
I told one of my bard friends about it and he figured it out pretty quick.  With the extended charm length you can really just keep it charmed until you want to release it.
<br />

<br />
*Oh btw.  I figured that this technique already existed but didn't know anybody who knew about it and never saw id discussed in any forums.</span></td>
