				<td colspan="2"><span>ROFLMFAO!!! 
<br />

<br />
<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" /><img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" /><img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" /><img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" /><img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Sorry for so much laughing, but this tactic has been around for quite some time.  I know I was doing it in my late 40's (a time when the 39 charm cost no mana), although the technique was available well before then.  Since Kocho moved sites, the threads posted here: <a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/eq/guides.aspx"><u>EQDiva Guides List</u></a> do not reflect the true creation dates.  I do know that most were before 11/5/2003.
<br />

<br />
The reason this technique is not really feasible 66 and beyond is because the mobs we can charm with our 64 charm spell are light blue (level 57 iirc) to us, thus not yielding much experience.  One can do better chant kiting singles, and gain even more xp while in a group.  As stated above, very very few bards have the OoW (70) charm.  I believe none have posted results of swarm kiting with it at least.  With what we do know however is that you have to be within melee range of the mob for the song to land, so swarming is going to be a bit more tricky if at all possible especially given how much dmg mobs hit at that level (68).  It is believed that SoE's purpose of the OoW charm is specifically for an added tool to use for crowd control.  More info will be released once more bards use the song and post results.
<br />

<br />
You are right, we shouldn't bash.  But I have to say seeing this post will most definitely bring a chuckle to many, including myself.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />

<br />
