				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">The reason this technique is not really feasible 66 and beyond is because the mobs we can charm with our 64 charm spell are light blue (level 57 iirc) to us, thus not yielding much experience.</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
57's and down to at least 55 (probably lower) are still dark blue.  I'm 67 now and still head to Gargs for a few minutes while waiting on raids to start up.  The reason it's not feasible is because the experience is pretty awful.  It takes 5-6 kills to get 1% regular.  And at 30 to 60 seconds a kill (usually closer to 60) that's still decent, but not nearly what we're used to.
<br />

<br />
And to the original poster, we're not bashing the technique.  We've all used it for years, what's amusing is that you think this is a secret, and that for some reason you insist that invis doesn't break charm anymore.  Also, what you described is generally referred to as &quot;Swarm kiting&quot;.  &quot;Charm kiting&quot; is when you charm a mob to go one on one against another mob.  And no, it's generally not possible to use summoning mobs as you'll get summoned by one and beaten on by all, so unless you're swarming something like Umbral where they don't really hurt, then a summoning mob will really kill your swarm kite.
<br />

<br />
