				<td colspan="2"><span>I've actually developed an even better method for gaining exp.  I call it &quot;AoE kiting&quot; and it involves aggroing a number of mobs and playing my AE songs until they all drop dead. 
<br />

<br />
A few things to consider if you want to try my method:
<br />
1. select non-summoning, non-casting mobs that run at the same speed
<br />
2. select a zone that has wide open spaces and flat terrain (Dulak's is recommended)
<br />
3. consider getting a SoW first so you don't have to Selos all the time
<br />
4. play around with auto-circle - it really helps a lot.
<br />

<br />
I've been able to kite 30-50 mobs at once using this method and the exp is phenomenal.  For you higher-level bards, try doing this in HoH but make sure you get your AE extended range AAs first.
